comment: Love (CLE) receives the pass inside the lower defensive box (the area between the 3-foot posted-up marks, the bottom tip of the circle and the endline) and therefore Antetokounmpo (MIL) may be in the restricted area when he attempts to block Love's shot.
Middleton (MIL) stops short and pushes his hip into Jefferson (CLE), dislodging him from defensive position.
James (CLE) draws Antetokounmpo (MIL) into the air toward him on the pump fake and contact occurs while in shooting motion.
LHH shows Jefferson (CLE) attempt to clamp Monroe's (MIL) arm under the basket prior to the rebound attempt. Monroe lets his arm go and Jefferson continues to slide down while holding onto it.
Monroe (MIL) beats James (CLE) to the spot and is firming up when James releases his pass.
LHH shows that Smith (CLE) gathers the ball in the air and lands on two feet. When stepping backwards, he fumbles the ball and he does not have control when the travel call was made.
Antetokounpo (MIL) makes contact with James (CLE) after he secures the rebound.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) places two hands on James (CLE) on his drive. When a player drives, the defensive player may place an extended forearm to the side of the driving player.
As Bayless (MIL) hands off the pass, he makes incidental contact with the trailing defender Jefferson (CLE).
RHH/RATR Monroe (MIL) does not make arm contact on Love's (CLE) shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Carter-Williams' (MIL) shot did not hit the rim was upheld.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Carter-Williams' (MIL) shot did not hit the rim was upheld.
LHH Dellavedova (CLE) turns into Bayless (MIL), but allows him to move to the basket without affecting his RSBQ or the shot attempt.

CLE asst coaches and bench players called for a TO. While officiating oncourt play, Referee heard a TO called and stopped play. Only the head coach and oncourt players can be granted a TO and stoppage deemed an inadvertent whistle. CLE then requests a TO.
LATR shows Thompson (CLE) wrap Monroe (MIL) in the post area.
James (CLE) establishes a legal screening position in Carter-Williams' (MIL) path.
Jefferson (CLE) makes contact with Antetokounmpo's (MIL) arm when he attempts to defend his shot.
LHH shows Carter-Williams (MIL) makes incidental contact with Williams' (CLE) hand after the shot is released.
RHH and RATR shows Antetokounmpo (MIL) makes contact with James' (CLE) arm and body as he attempts to block his shot, affecting his layup attempt.
Smith (CLE) makes contact with Carter-Williams' (MIL) arms that affects his layup attempt.
Bayless (MIL) holds James (CLE) and affects his FOM as he cuts away from the ball.
Bayless (MIL) makes incidental contact with James (CLE) that does not affect his layup attempt.
James (CLE) makes contact with Carter-Williams' (MIL) face after he secures the rebound while trying to knock the ball away.
Love (CLE) cleanly strips the ball from Monroe (MIL) on the drive to the basket.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Milwaukee was upheld and Cleveland was awarded possession.
